last_episode_to_air.name: Sea Of Thieves
last_episode_to_air.overview: The FBI uncovers a state-sanctioned plot to steal technology that makes U.S. submarines nearly undetectable to enemy sonar - and deploy it in Chinese subs.

name: FBI TRUE
overview: A real-life look into FBI agents’ high-pressure world with never-before-seen surveillance video, interrogations with hostage takers and terrorists, and personal photos from the agents’ collections.

episodes.name: The Manhattan Bomber
episodes.overview: On Sept 17th, 2016 a bomb detonates on 23rd Street in the Chelsea neighborhood of Manhattan, injuring over 30 people and causing mayhem. In the following hours and days, multiple bombs are discovered across Manhattan and New Jersey, all homemade devices designed to kill or maim as many people as possible. The FBI works with local law enforcement to track down a suspect who comes to be known as “The Chelsea Bomber,” culminating in a nail-biting standoff.

episodes.name: Horror in Yosemite
episodes.overview: In 1999, three women went missing in Yosemite National Park, launching the largest search and rescue operation in US history.  The bodies of two of the women are found in a burned car, and the third is only found when the killer sends a taunting note to the FBI.  Five months later, when a fourth woman is found beheaded near the park, the Bureau believes a serial killer may be on the loose.

episodes.name: Terror in Benghazi
episodes.overview: On the 11th anniversary of 9/11, armed men storm the U.S. Special Mission in Benghazi, Libya. The attack kills US Ambassador Christopher Stevens and three other Americans. The FBI launches an international investigation to track down the perpetrators, but in the chaos of post-Gaddafi Libya, arresting a suspect is no easy feat.

episodes.name: The Kidnapping of Hannah Anderson
episodes.overview: After a “family friend” murders a California mother and her 8-year-old son, the woman’s 16-year-old daughter is nowhere to be found. Authorities learn the killer has kidnapped Hannah Anderson and taken her to the remote wilderness of Idaho. The FBI’s Hostage Rescue Team receives a tip and tries to track down the pair before it’s too late.

guest_stars.character: Self - Unit Chief Hostage Rescue Team FBI
guest_stars.name: Chuck Davis

episodes.name: Waco (1)
episodes.overview: An ATF raid on the compound of an armed apocalyptic religious group in Waco, Texas turns deadly. After a terrifying shootout, four federal agents are dead and more than a dozen are wounded. The FBI steps in with its tactical and negotiation teams, but as both sides dig in, concerns grow about the intentions of the group's leader and the welfare of the children inside.

episodes.name: Waco (2)
episodes.overview: After a fifty-one day standoff, the FBI decides to move in on the Branch Davidians and their leader, David Koresh. Three agents tell heart wrenching stories about what happened on that historic day and the deadly blaze that ensued.

episodes.name: Hunting Whitey Bulger
episodes.overview: Notorious Boston mobster Whitey Bulger, accused of 19 murders, has been on the run for 15 years. He went on the lam after being tipped off by a corrupt FBI agent. The Bureau brings in two hard-charging agents from outside the city to track down Bulger. Will their new approach lead to the capture of the FBI’s Most Wanted fugitive?

episodes.name: The Beltway Snipers
episodes.overview: An unknown sniper terrorizes the citizens of Washington, D.C. over three weeks in October, 2002. FBI investigators hunt for the murderer as the killings continue. With limited evidence and a series of false leads, the investigation stalls. Will a series of cryptic clues left by the shooter help the authorities end the killing spree?

guest_stars.character: Self - Special Agent Cold Case Squad FBI
guest_stars.name: Melissa Thomas

episodes.name: The Boy in the Bunker (1)
episodes.overview: In 2013, Jimmy Lee Dykes shoots and kills a rural Alabama school bus driver and takes a five-year-old boy hostage in a carefully constructed bunker. The FBI discovers that the bunker is lined with explosives and Dykes is heavily armed. After a six day standoff, Dykes sets a deadline for the following day to broadcast his grievances on TV news, or he will kill the boy and himself.

episodes.name: The Boy in the Bunker (2)
episodes.overview: The FBI Hostage Rescue Team works with brilliant FBI profiler Molly Amman to extract a five-year-old boy from a bunker built by a heavily armed captor named Jimmy Lee Dykes. The profiler must convince FBI director Robert Muller that negotiations with the erratic Dykes are doomed to fail.

episodes.name: Boston Marathon Manhunt (1)
episodes.overview: When two bombs cut a swathe of death and destruction through the crowd of runners and spectators at the finish line of the Boston Marathon, the FBI steps up to lead a massive manhunt for the perpetrators. As the nation watches transfixed, the Bureau and its law enforcement partners work against time to find the bombers before they can strike again. When the suspects finally emerge, they lead authorities on a deadly high-stakes chase through the streets of Boston.

episodes.name: Boston Marathon Manhunt (2)
episodes.overview: In the tense hours following the bombings, Sergeant John MacLellan heads out on his night shift. That same evening, an MIT police officer is murdered by two attackers. No one knows yet that the cop killers and the bombers are one and the same, and Sgt. MacLellan comes face to face with the perpetrators. The shootout that ensues leads to a citywide manhunt.

episodes.name: Gangs of Newburgh
episodes.overview: Newburgh NY is a small town with a big problem. Gang warfare has made it the most violent city in the state. Tapping into U.S. military surge strategy, FBI agent James Gagliano hatches a plan to dismantle the rival gangs in one day full of gangster shock and awe.

episodes.name: The Outlaws Biker Bust
episodes.overview: Two FBI agents go undercover to infiltrate a dangerous criminal motorcycle gang. The Outlaws – archrivals of the infamous Hells Angels – are running wild in Taunton, Massachusetts, bringing drugs and violence to the formerly peaceful town. The stakes are high as the agents plan a daring takedown. Will they make a big bust or will their cover get blown?

episodes.name: The Southside Bandit
episodes.overview: When an armed bank robber terrorizes the Boston area, the violent holdups leave bank employees and customers fearing for their lives. Without any solid leads, the FBI's Bank Robbery Task Force must use all its resources to catch the perpetrator in the act. But can law enforcement catch up to the Southside Bandit before the situation turns deadly?

episodes.name: Mob Cops
episodes.overview: Rumors swirled for years that two former NYPD detectives, Stephen Caracappa and Louis Eppolito were working for the Mafia, committing crimes that included murder, kidnapping and money laundering for their mob bosses. Both men retire from the police department and move to Las Vegas, but when a former Mafia underboss admits that Caracappa and Eppolitto carried out a number of murders on his orders, the FBI formulates a plan to bring the “Mob Cops” to justice.

episodes.name: Attack on Oklahoma (1)
episodes.overview: An early-morning explosion at a federal building in downtown Oklahoma City kills and injures hundreds. FBI investigators quickly determine that the building has been bombed. The Bureau coordinates a complex rescue mission to save survivors of the blast. At the same time, agents comb through the wreckage, searching for clues about the bomber.

episodes.name: Attack on Oklahoma (2)
episodes.overview: The FBI learns Timothy McVeigh hopes to instigate a civil war in America with his bombing of the Federal building in Oklahoma City. His arrest will set in motion a nationwide hunt that will take investigators from Oklahoma across the country, questioning collaborators, uncovering evidence and unveiling the history of a young man disillusioned with the government.

episodes.name: The Golden State Killer
episodes.overview: In one of the most infamous serial killer cases in American history, the FBI works with local law enforcement in California to try and apprehend the so-called “Golden State Killer.” It’s a case that spans four decades, as the killer and rapist continually manages to elude law enforcement. Authorities resort to an unprecedented use of DNA data in an attempt to finally track down the man responsible for 13 murders and 51 sexual assaults.

episodes.name: The San Bernardino Mass Shooting
episodes.overview: Masked shooters attack an office Christmas party in San Bernardino, killing and wounding dozens of people. FBI investigators descend on the scene, looking for clues about the identity of the killers. But as they try to find out who the active shooters are, they’re faced with a more urgent question…where are they and do they plan to strike again?

episodes.name: The Rise of Al Qaeda (1)
episodes.overview: In the aftermath of the bombings of two US embassies in Africa, three FBI agents suspect an injured bystander may well be one of the lead terrorists.

episodes.name: The Rise of Al Qaeda (2)
episodes.overview: Once the FBI discovers a bomb factory connected to the 1998 attacks on American embassies in Africa, it exposes the vast reach of a little-known terrorist group called Al Qaeda.

episodes.name: The Hitman
episodes.overview: FBI undercover agents conduct a sting operation on an ex-con in Boston who has plans to resume his life of crime.

episodes.name: Fire in the Sky: TWA Flight 800
episodes.overview: Twelve minutes after its departure from JFK airport, TWA Flight 800 suddenly explodes. FBI investigators must determine if it's a tragic accident or the result of sabotage.

episodes.name: The Corrupt Senator
episodes.overview: Senator Dianne Wilkerson is beloved by her constituents in Massachusetts, but when the FBI receives a tip that she is accepting bribes, agents from the Public Corruption squad open an investigation.

episodes.name: The Bronx Butcher
episodes.overview: The FBI investigates the discovery of a dismembered body in Albania and learns a nearly identical crime in Brooklyn 16 years earlier could point them to the killer.

episodes.name: Cartel Kidnapping
episodes.overview: A young man in South Carolina is kidnapped by members of a Mexican cartel and the FBI brings in its Hostage Rescue Team to try and save him.

episodes.name: Hostages at Sea
episodes.overview: Pirates murder four Americans off the coast of Somalia and the FBI chases the criminal mastermind across Africa.

episodes.name: Al Qaeda in Queens
episodes.overview: The FBI pursues an Al Qaeda terrorist group with plans to bomb the New York subway system.

episodes.name: Home Depot Bomb Plot
episodes.overview: After one lethal pipe bomb is found inside a Long Island Home Depot, the FBI mobilizes to prevent a potential second bomb from being detonated on Black Friday.

episodes.name: Terror In Times Square: Chasing a Madman
episodes.overview: When a would-be terrorist attempts to set off a bomb in Times Square, the FBI embarks on a high-speed, high-stakes race against time to catch the bomber.

episodes.name: Operation Knockout: The Biggest Takedown
episodes.overview: Following the murder of a Deputy Sheriff by a Latino gang, the FBI leads a task force in Operation Knockout, the largest anti-gang operation in US history.

episodes.name: Ruby Ridge: The Real Story (1)
episodes.overview: Following the fatal shooting of a U.S. Deputy Marshal during a stakeout of a wanted fugitive, the FBI's Hostage Rescue Team is called in.

episodes.name: Ruby Ridge: The Real Story (2)
episodes.overview: As the FBI prepares for a final assault on the remote cabin where fugitive Randy Weaver is holed up, a gruesome discovery puts the entire mission on hold.

episodes.name: Hunting GRAYSUIT: America's Deadly Traitor (1)
episodes.overview: An FBI investigative specialist with no undercover training goes undercover and comes face-to-face with Robert Hanssen, a suspected spy.

episodes.name: Hunting GRAYSUIT: America's Deadly Traitor (2)
episodes.overview: Eric O'Neill, an FBI investigative specialist with no undercover training, manages to win the trust of suspected spy, Robert Hanssen — or so he thinks.

episodes.name: The Disappearance of Chyenne Kircher (1)
episodes.overview: In 2011, 14-year old Chyenne Kircher disappears from her dysfunctional small-town Illinois home, leaving a convincing runaway note.

episodes.name: The Disappearance of Chyenne Kircher (2)
episodes.overview: The FBI doggedly wade through their prime suspect's emotional outbursts, half-truths and outright lies to find out what happened to Chyenne Kircher.

episodes.name: Chasing The Olympic Bomber (1)
episodes.overview: A pipe bomb at a concert is the first of a string of explosions during the 1996 Atlanta Olympics; the FBI have a serial bomber on their hands.

episodes.name: Chasing The Olympic Bomber (2)
episodes.overview: After another deadly bombing, a suspicious character in a wig is seen walking away, sparking one of the biggest manhunts in U.S. history.

episodes.name: Art Heist: Catching A Mastermind
episodes.overview: After a tip from an informant, FBI agents work to track down priceless works of art stolen from Denmark’s national museum.

episodes.name: FIFA: Sports' Biggest Scandal
episodes.overview: In 2015, the FBI uncovered a deep and widespread criminal conspiracy among members of FIFA - including wire fraud, racketeering, and money laundering.

episodes.name: Hunting a Terrorist Mastermind
episodes.overview: When a massive bomb planted in a van explodes below the North Tower of the World Trade Center in 1993, the FBI sets out to find the bomber

episodes.name: Stopping a Snipper
episodes.overview: After a family doctor well-known for performing abortions is gunned down in his suburban Buffalo home in 1998, all clues point to an anti-abortion extremist as the sniper.

episodes.name: Seattle Sex Trafficker: 'You're Gonna Be Rich'
episodes.overview: In 2014, a suburban police detective learns of a Seattle filmmaker who convinces teenage girls to engage in prostitution with fraudulent promises that they'll cash in when he makes a movie on the subject.

episodes.name: Finding Aldrich Ames: The Hunt for a Mole
episodes.overview: When the CIA's most valuable Russian assets start disappearing one by one, the Agency starts hunting for the mole who's been betraying them since 1985.

episodes.name: The Birmingham Church Bombing: The Long Arc of Justice (1)
episodes.overview: After the 1963 bombing of a Baptist Church in Birmingham takes the lives of four young girls, the FBI embarks on a four-decades-long quest for justice.

episodes.name: The Birmingham Church Bombing: The Long Arc of Justice (2)
episodes.overview: FBI agents uncover new evidence from the Birmingham Church Bombing that could finally bring justice to the young girls killed in this act of racial hatred.

episodes.name: Showdown in the West (1)
episodes.overview: When federal authorities seize a renegade rancher's family cattle in 2014, heavily armed anti-government militias come to his aid and a dangerous showdown ensues.

episodes.name: Showdown in the West (2)
episodes.overview: The FBI faces down a group of anti-government ranchers and heavily-armed militias who've taken over a federal wildlife refuge in Oregon. A car chase through the mountains ensues, and when one rancher refuses to surrender, the showdown turns deadly.

episodes.name: Love & Murder in Old San Juan
episodes.overview: The stabbing death of a wealthy young husband of a beauty queen in Old San Juan leads to a full blown murder-for-fire conspiracy investigation and an international manhunt by the FBI.

episodes.name: Operation Oxy Alley
episodes.overview: Agents uncover the largest oxycodone trafficking operation in American history. But building a case is easier said than done, when the drugs are legal. The FBI zeroes in on twin brother pain clinic owners, suspecting they're running a pill mill.

episodes.name: Who Bombed Pan Am 103?
episodes.overview: Days before Christmas, a Pan Am plane crashes in the remote Scottish village of Lockerbie. 290 people are killed, including 190 Americans. The investigation leads the FBI across the world in a quest to find out what caused the unspeakable tragedy.

episodes.name: McDonald's Monopoly Scam (1)
episodes.overview: The FBI gets a tip that the McDonald's Monopoly promo games are rigged, and a mysterious figure dubbed "Uncle Jerry" is behind this scam. There's a race against the clock, as McDonald's agrees to run one more game, hoping to catch him in the act.

episodes.name: McDonald's Monopoly Scam (2)
episodes.overview: The FBI has one shot to catch the McDonald's Monopoly scammers in the act. Agents deploy some very creative undercover techniques to gather evidence. Days away from the takedown, a fax sent to the wrong organization could derail the entire case.

episodes.name: Bernie Madoff
episodes.overview: After Bernie Madoff confesses to the FBI that he's responsible for a $64 billion Ponzi scheme he is quickly arrested, but the FBI's job is just beginning. They have the long task of recovering stolen assets to help those whose lives he had shattered.

episodes.name: Officer Pulido
episodes.overview: A small-time crook hoping for a break alerts the FBI to a cadre of corrupt cops within the Boston Police. But taking down three SWAT-trained members of a police force comes with unavoidable risks.

episodes.name: Sea Of Thieves
episodes.overview: The FBI uncovers a state-sanctioned plot to steal technology that makes U.S. submarines nearly undetectable to enemy sonar - and deploy it in Chinese subs.
